---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Complete Guide to Barbershop Marketing Automation in Canada | Lead Flow North">
  <article class="py-12 md:py-20">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Back Link -->
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mb-8">
        <a href="/industries/salons-spas/barbershops" class="inline-flex items-center text-sky-600 hover:text-sky-700 dark:text-sky-300 font-medium">
          <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path></svg>
          Back to Barbershops
        </a>
      </div>
      
      <header class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center mb-12">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 mb-6">
          <span class="bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">Barbershops</span>
          <span class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm">10 min read</span>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
          The Complete Guide to Barbershop Marketing Automation
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
          Capture walk-ins, bring back regulars, and build digital loyalty that replaces punch cards.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
          
          <p class="lead text-xl text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 mb-8">
            Barbershops run on walk-ins and repeat customers. But when you're cutting hair, you can't answer the phone. Automation bridges the gap.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Missed Call Text-Back Is Game-Changing</h2>

          <p>
            When a guy calls to check if you're busy and you're mid-fade, you miss the call. Automated text-back—"Hey, we're with a client. Want to book online?"—converts that missed call into a booking.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">The 3-Week Haircut Reminder</h2>

          <p>
            Guys mean to come every 2-3 weeks but life gets busy. "Hey bro, been 3 weeks—time for a fresh cut?" texts at the perfect interval keep chairs full and fades fresh.
          </p>

          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-white mt-12 mb-4">Digital Loyalty That Works</h2>

          <p>
            Punch cards get lost. Digital tracking—"10th cut free"—tracks automatically, sends progress updates, and delivers rewards without any friction.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-600 to-orange-600 p-8 rounded-xl text-white my-12">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">Ready to Fill Your Chairs?</h3>
            <p class="text-amber-100 mb-6">
              Get a free consultation and see exactly how we'd capture walk-ins and build loyalty.
            </p>
            <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center bg-white text-amber-600 px-6 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold hover:bg-slate-100 transition">
              Book Your Free Demo
            </a>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
